Data Structures

Here are the data structures with brief descriptions:
EOSKernelMain class of the EOS Kernel module
EOSLuaEnvironmentThis class wraps the Lua interpreter environment instance
EOSLuaScriptThis class represents a single EOS Lua source script
EOSLuaStackRestorerThis class is used to keep Lua stack always in a consistent state (based on code from Richard Shephard, published on CodeProject website: http://www.codeproject.com/cpp/luaincpp.asp)
EOSLuaThisRestorerThis class is used to load the correct "this" reference each time the execution enters on a new script (based on code from Richard Shephard, published on CodeProject website: http://www.codeproject.com/cpp/luaincpp.asp)
EOSMessageThis class models the EOS Message Structure
EOSProcessClass used to model an EOS Process (a single script instance)
EOSScriptManagerClass used to load and manage source scripts
luaScriptBufferSimple structure to hold a source script buffer in memory
MessageFieldThis class represents a single field of an EOS Message Structure
VariantDataClass used to handle Lua Variant (boolean/numeric/string) data in EOS Kernel
